---
question: "Is LASIK a permanent fix, or will I need glasses again eventually?"
tags: ["lasik"]
---
LASIK corrects your current prescription and the results are generally long-lasting. However, it doesn't prevent normal age-related vision changes later in life, such as presbyopia (needing reading glasses in your 40s) or cataracts. LASIK addresses your refractive error at the time of surgery, not future, unrelated changes.
